name: servicenetworking_services_projects_global_networks_dnsZones_list
description: * Service producers can use this method to retrieve a list of available DNS zones in the shared producer host project and the matching peering zones in the consumer project. *

parent.description: Required. Parent resource identifying the connection which owns this collection of DNS zones in the format services/{service}/projects/{project}/global/networks/{network} Service: The service that is managing connectivity for the service producer's organization. For Google services that support this functionality, this value is `servicenetworking.googleapis.com`. Projects: the consumer project containing the consumer network. Network: The consumer network accessible from the tenant project.
